# SEO Best Practices (React SPA + CloudFront)

- Set a unique `<title>` and meta description for every indexable route.
- Set canonical URLs for all public pages. Avoid duplicate canonical targets.
- Keep URLs human-readable and stable (`/teachers`, `/teacher/:slug`, `/graduates/:year`).
- Keep one clear `h1` per page and a logical heading hierarchy.
- Preserve structured data (JSON-LD) for:
  - organization/site,
  - breadcrumbs,
  - entity pages.
- Provide and maintain `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt`.
- Ensure CloudFront and SPA routing do not break direct URL access.
- Do not block important assets with robots rules.
- Use descriptive `alt` text for meaningful images.
- Optimize media for performance (modern formats, dimensions, lazy loading where appropriate).
- Verify Open Graph and Twitter metadata for share previews.
- Treat SEO metadata as product requirements, not optional polish.
